comment_data.body:
There may actually be a couple of reasons to define `PyInit_`:

1. it probably helps people out who are doing embedding (or similar things) and using the function (hopefully with `InitTab`...).
2. setuptools on Windows adds the command-line argument `/EXPORT:PyInit_...` which will fail if the symbol doesn't exist.

Although it would mean removing a lot of conditional compilation, including adding back in the `PyModuleDef`
